  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I'm having trouble signing an offline transaction and using sendRawTransaction to submit it.\n\nThe tx gets accepted by geth but instead of showing `\"to: 0x1234567890\"` in the console it shows `\"to: &1234567890\"`\n\nI'm not sure if the problem is in ethereumjs-tx which creates the raw tx or in geth sendRawTransaction but either way geth should detect the &1234 address and throw error.\n\nSee related: https://github.com/ethereumjs/ethereumjs-tx/issues/15\n",
