    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "There's no overflow. The transaction is valid, just misses a \"few\" ones in between. That is a completely valid use case as might happen when transactions propagate through the network out of order and need to be pieced back together.\n\nFormatting wise we did some internal changes and that probably resulted in printing an address (internally it is one), but I agree it's not the best. @bas-vk How hard would it be / would it make sense to have a custom formatting rule that flattens pointers for the console, specifically the transaction To field which we've changed a few weeks ago?\n",
